%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump's%20tariffs%20are%20hitting%20China's%20friends%20hard%20%26amp%3Bmdash%3B%20and%20giving%20Beijing%20a%20golden%20opportunity%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22President%20Donald%20Trump%20speaking%20to%20the%20press%20in%20the%20Oval%20Office%3B%20Chinese%20leader%20Xi%20Jinping%20making%20a%20toast%20during%20a%20dinner%20in%20Macau.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ef9ebab8b41a9673fca2ba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EExperts%20said%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20reciprocal%20tariffs%20will%20likely%20push%20China's%20allies%20closer%20to%20Beijing.%3Cp%3EWin%20McNamee%20via%20Getty%20Images%3B%20Anthony%20Kwan%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETrump's%20new%20tariffs%20give%20China%20room%20to%20play%20the%20foil%20to%20the%20US%20and%20bolster%20its%20hold%20on%20the%20region.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECambodia%2C%20Laos%2C%20and%20Myanmar%20hold%20great%20strategic%20value%20for%20China%20as%20it%20seeks%20to%20expand%20its%20influence.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20China%20responded%20to%20Trump's%20tariffs%20with%20a%2034%25%20tariff%20on%20all%20goods%20imported%20from%20the%20US.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump's%3C%2Fa%3E%20sweeping%20tariffs%20are%20expected%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-liberation-day-reciprocal-tariffs-speech-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecut%20deep%20against%20both%20friend%20and%20foe%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20several%20of%20the%20nations%20that%20stand%20to%20suffer%20the%20most%20are%20right%20on%20China's%20doorstep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECambodia%2C%20Laos%2C%20and%20Myanmar%20are%20on%20track%20to%20face%20tariff%20rates%20of%2049%25%2C%2048%25%2C%20and%2045%25%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20three%20have%20maintained%20close%20economic%20and%20political%20ties%20with%20China%2C%20which%20must%20itself%20contend%20with%20a%20total%20tariff%20rate%20of%2054%25%20%E2%80%94%20the%20highest%20out%20of%20anywhere%20in%20the%20world.%20China's%20response%20was%20swift%3A%20On%20Friday%2C%20Beijing%20retaliated%20against%20Trump's%20tariffs%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-retaliates-own-tariffs-against-trump-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E34%25%20tariff%20on%20all%20goods%20imported%20from%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnly%20Lesotho%2C%20Madagascar%2C%20and%20Vietnam%2C%20which%20the%20US%20is%20targeting%20with%20rates%20of%2050%25%2C%2047%25%2C%20and%2046%25%2C%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20a%20higher%20or%20equal%20level%20of%20import%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20and%20researchers%20who%20study%20the%20area%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20tariffs%20will%20likely%20push%20China's%20allies%20closer%20to%20Beijing%2C%20giving%20Chinese%20leader%20Xi%20Jinping%20an%20opportunity%20to%20strengthen%20his%20hold%20on%20a%20region%20that%20his%20country%20greatly%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStrategically%2C%20the%20US%20is%20now%20handing%20a%20victory%20to%20China%20in%20the%20US-China%20competition%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Vina%20Nadjibulla%2C%20the%20vice%20president%20of%20research%20and%20strategy%20at%20the%20Asia%20Pacific%20Foundation%20of%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20US%20is%20preoccupied%20with%20competing%20with%20China%2C%20it%20is%20ceding%20ground%20and%20losing%20influence%20by%20essentially%20making%20China%20the%20only%20possible%20alternative%20for%20many%20of%20these%20economies%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%2C%20US%20Treasury%20Department%2C%20and%20US%20State%20Department%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20BI%20for%20this%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227444edcc-8c4c-4d62-9c6f-6d200482c1e4%5C%22%3EIs%20Trump%20punishing%20ties%20to%20China%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20many%20of%20the%20nations%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20tariff%20list%20hold%20close%20ties%20with%20Beijing%2C%20US%20allies%20are%20hit%2C%20too.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BTraditional%20US%20allies%20such%20as%20the%20European%20Union%2C%20Japan%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20and%20even%20Australia%20were%20all%20subject%20to%20these%20tariffs%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Baogang%20He%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20international%20relations%20at%20Deakin%20University%20in%20Melbourne%2C%20Australia.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20rates%20appear%20to%20be%20tied%20to%20US%20trade%20deficits%20with%20each%20country%2C%20though%20the%20president%20has%20characterized%20the%20tariffs%20as%20reciprocal%20to%20taxes%20imposed%20by%20those%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20rates%20are%20all%20about%20trade%20deficits%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Emily%20Kilcrease%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20who%20studies%20the%20US-China%20relationship%20for%20the%20Center%20for%20a%20New%20American%20Security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECambodia's%20export%20surplus%20to%20the%20US%20is%20worth%20%2412.34%20billion%2C%20Laos'%20is%20worth%20%24760%20million%2C%20and%20Myanmar's%20is%20worth%20%24580%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIan%20Bremmer%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20president%20of%20Eurasia%20Group%2C%20said%20at%20the%20World%20Economic%20Forum%20in%20January%20that%20he%20foresaw%20Trump%20targeting%20China%20through%20third-party%20countries%20that%20Beijing%20is%20using%20to%20manufacture%20goods%20to%20be%20shipped%20to%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20only%20way%20the%20Chinese%20economy%20is%20succeeding%20right%20now%20is%20through%20their%20%241%20trillion%20export%20surplus%2C%26quot%3B%20Bremmer%20said%20at%20the%20time.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20you%20see%20Trump%20and%20his%20team%20focusing%20a%20lot%20on%20Mexico%2C%20and%20India%2C%20and%20Vietnam.%20The%20other%20conversations%20they%20are%20having%20bilaterally%2C%20one%20of%20the%20top%20priorities%20is%3A%20squeeze%20China%20coming%20in.%20That's%20very%20hard%20for%20China%20to%20respond%20to.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBremmer%20told%20BI%20on%20Thursday%20that%20he%20stands%20by%20his%20earlier%20comments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAbsolutely.%20And%20the%20Chinese%20government%20has%20felt%20the%20same%20way%20about%20the%20United%20States%20pushing%20Mexico%20hard%20on%20getting%20Chinese%20pass-through%20trade%20out%20of%20the%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20Bremmer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECountries%20such%20as%20Mexico%2C%20Cambodia%2C%20and%20Vietnam%20have%20been%20key%20players%20in%20a%20manufacturing%20network%20known%20as%20%26quot%3BChina%2B1%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20emerged%20in%20response%20to%20Trump's%20restrictions%20on%20Chinese%20exports%20during%20his%20first%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20circumvent%20those%20measures%2C%20Chinese%20firms%20diversified%20their%20supply%20chains%20by%20sending%20raw%20materials%20to%20friendly%20countries%20and%20having%20the%20host%20nations%20manufacture%20products%20instead.%20The%20goods%20could%20then%20be%20exported%20to%20the%20US%20at%20lower%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2243ff6329-999f-4b6c-a375-580aae50c97c%5C%22%3EChina%2B1%20at%20risk%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20tariffs%20will%20likely%20stifle%20China%2B1%20among%20Beijing's%20close%20allies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECambodia%2C%20for%20example%2C%20relies%20largely%20on%20China%2B1%20for%20its%20exports%20of%20clothing%2C%20sporting%20goods%2C%20luggage%2C%20and%20other%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCambodia%20has%20no%20raw%20materials.%20All%20the%20raw%20materials%2C%20the%20supplies%20have%20to%20come%20from%20mainly%20China%2C%20even%20buttons%20or%20threads%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mu%20Sochua%2C%20a%20former%20Cambodian%20minister%20who%20works%20in%20exile%20due%20to%20her%20criticism%20of%20the%20incumbent%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20week%20from%20now%2C%20if%20Cambodia%20cannot%20negotiate%20to%20have%20the%20tariffs%20go%20down%20significantly%2C%20there%20will%20be%20an%20immediate%20economic%20crisis%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20She%20added%20that%20if%20factories%20there%20shut%20down%20or%20pause%20production%2C%20over%20a%20million%20factory%20workers%20could%20lose%20their%20livelihoods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVietnam%2C%20a%20major%20base%20for%20making%20Chinese-partnered%20goods%2C%20is%20likely%20to%20try%20negotiating%20its%2046%25%20tariff%20with%20the%20US.%20Hanoi%20has%20asked%20Washington%20to%20pause%20the%20taxes%20and%20come%20to%20the%20table%2C%20and%20Trump%20has%20said%20he%20is%20open%20to%20discussion%20on%20his%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223bba20c8-3503-4164-a8a1-c2d811da5d23%5C%22%3EBeijing's%20opportunity%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EVietnam%20balances%20its%20ties%20more%20evenly%20with%20the%20US%20and%20China%2C%20and%20its%20relationship%20with%20Beijing%20suffers%20from%20disputes%20over%20the%20South%20China%20Sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaos%2C%20Cambodia%2C%20and%20Myanmar%20are%20far%20deeper%20in%20China's%20camp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20works%20closely%20with%20Myanmar's%20ruling%20junta%20and%20opposing%20rebel%20factions%20to%20maintain%20access%20to%20vast%20rare%20earth%20mineral%20reserves%20in%20the%20country's%20north.%20Myanmar%20is%20also%20the%20only%20geographical%20barrier%20between%20China%20and%20the%20Indian%20Ocean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20administration%20has%20shown%20little%20interest%20in%20extending%20influence%20over%20Myanmar.%20The%20US%20was%20absent%20from%20the%20list%20of%20parties%20sending%20aid%20to%20the%20country%20after%20a%20devastating%20earthquake%20struck%20Myanmar%20on%20March%2028.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Cambodia%20hosts%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-largest-fleet-secretly-building-naval-base-cambodia-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enaval%20base%3C%2Fa%3E%20built%20by%20China%20on%20its%20southern%20coast%20%E2%80%94%20an%20important%20facility%20that%20would%20extend%20China's%20reach%20into%20Southeast%20Asia%20and%20on%20Taiwan's%20flank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECambodia's%20long-ruling%20and%20iron-fisted%20prime%20minister%2C%20Hun%20Sen%2C%20also%20enjoys%20close%20personal%20ties%20with%20Beijing.%20The%20country's%20foreign%20ministry%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKilcrease%20of%20CNAS%20said%20the%20incentives%20for%20China's%20allies%20to%20look%20to%20Beijing%20are%20already%20shaping%20up%20on%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20did%20some%20back-of-the-envelope%20math%2C%20and%20it%20appears%20that%20most%20countries%20in%20the%20world%20now%20face%20a%20higher%20tariff%20rate%20from%20the%20US%20than%20from%20China%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20yes%2C%20there%20is%20a%20significant%20risk%20that%20these%20countries%20move%20closer%20to%20China.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeijing%20is%20also%20generally%20well-received%20in%20Southeast%20Asia%2C%20said%20Kristina%20Fong%2C%20the%20lead%20researcher%20on%20the%20region's%20economic%20affairs%20at%20Singapore's%20ISEAS-Yusof%20Ishak%20Institute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20cited%20a%20study%20of%20attitudes%20among%20over%202%2C000%20Southeast%20Asians%20conducted%20by%20her%20institute%20in%20early%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B56.4%25%20of%20Southeast%20Asian%20respondents%20cited%20China%20as%20Southeast%20Asia's%20most%20influential%20economic%20power.%20China%20was%20the%20choice%20for%20all%20ASEAN%20countries%2C%26quot%3B%20Fong%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2255f9c369-2320-4d61-b53d-c26caf312058%5C%22%3EThe%20ball%20is%20in%20China's%20court%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20interim%2C%20the%20ball%20is%20in%20Beijing's%20court%2C%20said%20Austin%20Strange%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Hong%20Kong's%20Department%20of%20Politics%20and%20Public%20Administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChina's%20government%2C%20at%20least%20in%20the%20short%20term%2C%20can%20make%20public%20relations%20gains%20%E2%80%94%20just%20as%20in%20other%20areas%20of%20foreign%20policy%2C%20such%20as%20international%20development%20%E2%80%94%20by%20presenting%20itself%20as%20a%20stable%2C%20reliable%20partner%20amid%20US%20foreign%20policy%20upheaval%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeijing's%20state%20media%20reported%20last%20weekend%20that%20its%20authorities%20agreed%20with%20South%20Korea%20and%20Japan%20to%20issue%20a%20joint%20response%20to%20any%20US%20tariffs.%20However%2C%20Tokyo%20has%20said%20its%20leaders%20simply%20met%20to%20share%20views.%20Seoul%20said%20reports%20of%20a%20team-up%20were%20%26quot%3Bsomewhat%20exaggerated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20I%20expect%20China%20and%20other%20economies%20to%20continue%20to%20find%20workarounds%2C%26quot%3B%20Strange%20added.%20%26quot%3BThey%20have%2C%20after%20all%2C%20had%20months%20if%20not%20longer%20to%20prepare%2C%20as%20Trump%20has%20consistently%20pledged%20to%20levy%20sweeping%20tariffs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-golden-opportunity-china-cambodia-laos-myanmar-hard-hit-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743766928000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ef9ebab8b41a9673fca2ba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-golden-opportunity-china-cambodia-laos-myanmar-hard-hit-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Cambodia%2C%20Laos%2C%20and%20Myanmar%20were%20hit%20with%20tariffs%20of%2049%25%2C%2048%25%2C%20and%2045%25%20respectively.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mloh%40businessinsider.com%20(Matthew%20Loh%2CKwan%20Wei%20Kevin%20Tan)%22%2C%2