0later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Prime%20Minister%20also%20urged%20in%20this%20regard%20that%20any%20rhetoric%20that%20vitiates%20the%20environment%20is%20best%20avoided.%20On%20the%20border%2C%20strict%20enforcement%20of%20the%20law%20and%20prevention%20of%20illegal%20border%20crossing%2C%20especially%20at%20night%2C%20in%20necessary%20for%20maintaining%20border%20stability%20and%20security%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Misri%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Foreign%20Secretary%20said%20that%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20underlined%20India's%20concerns%20related%20to%20the%20safety%20and%20security%20of%20minorities%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20including%20Hindus%2C%20and%20expressed%20his%20expectations%20that%20the%20government%20of%20Bangladesh%20would%20ensure%20their%20security.%20The%20Prime%20Minister%20also%20pressed%20for%20a%20thorough%20investigation%20into%20all%20cases%20of%20atrocities%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bangladesh%20government%2C%20too%2C%20issued%20a%20statement%20on%20the%20conversation%20between%20the%20two%20leaders.%20According%20to%20it%2C%20Mr%20Yunus%20told%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20that%20Bangladesh%20%26quot%3Bdeeply%20values%20its%20relationship%20with%20India%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BThe%20deep-rooted%20friendship%20between%20our%20two%20countries%20is%20founded%20on%20intertwined%20histories%2C%20geographical%20proximity%2C%20and%20cultural%20affinity.%20We%20remain%20thankful%20for%20the%20unwavering%20support%20of%20the%20government%20and%20people%20of%20India%20during%20our%20most%20challenging%20time%20in%201971%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bangladesh%20leader%20sought%20India's%20support%20for%20a%20Free%20Trade%20Agreement%20among%20the%20seven%20BIMSTEC%20members%20and%20also%20called%20for%20discussions%20to%20renew%20the%20Ganges%20Water%20Treaty%20and%20to%20conclude%20the%20Teesta%20Water%20Sharing%20Agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Yunus%20also%20asked%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20about%20the%20status%20of%20Bangladesh's%20request%20for%20the%20extradition%20of%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20and%20said%20she%20had%20been%20making%20inflammatory%20remarks%20in%20the%20media%20and%20attempting%20to%20destabilise%20the%20situation%20in%20Bangladesh.%20%26quot%3BWe%20request%20that%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20take%20appropriate%20measures%20to%20restrain%20her%20from%20continuing%20to%20make%20such%20incendiary%20statements%20while%20she%20remains%20in%20your%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi's%20concern%20over%20the%20condition%20of%20minorities%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20Mr%20Yunus%20said%20the%20reports%20of%20attacks%20on%20the%20minorities%20were%20hugely%20inflated%20and%20%26quot%3Bthe%20bulk%20of%20them%20were%20fake%20news%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Chief%20Adviser%20said%20he%20has%20instituted%20an%20effective%20system%20for%20monitoring%20every%20incident%20of%20religious%20and%20gender%20violence%20in%20the%20country%2C%20and%20his%20government%20was%20taking%20serious%20actions%20to%20stop%20any%20occurrence%20of%20such%20incidents%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20the%20first%20meeting%20between%20the%20two%20leaders%20since%20Mr%20Yunus%20took%20charge%20of%20Bangladesh%20following%20the%20ouster%20of%20the%20Sheikh%20Hasina%20government%20in%20August%20last%20year.%20The%20meeting%20assumes%20significance%20amid%20Dhaka's%20growing%20closeness%20with%20Beijing%2C%20a%20development%20Delhi%20has%20been%20watching%20closely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERelations%20between%20Delhi%20and%20Dhaka%20have%20taken%20a%20frosty%20turn%20since%20the%20Sheikh%20Hasina-led%20Awami%20League%20government%20was%20overthrown%20after%20a%20nationwide%20movement%20and%20an%20interim%20government%20took%20over.%20The%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20fled%20to%20India.%20In%20the%20months%20following%20the%20change%20of%20guard%2C%20India%20expressed%20concerns%20over%20reports%20of%20attacks%20on%20minorities%20in%20Bangladesh.%20Dhaka%20has%20stressed%20that%20%26quot%3BBangladesh's%20minorities%20are%20Bangladesh's%20issue%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Yunus'%20recent%20remarks%20on%20the%20Northeastern%20states%20in%20India%20stoked%20tensions%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20and%20drew%20strong%20responses%20from%20the%20region's%20leaders.%20A%20video%20of%20Mr%20Yunus's%20remarks%2C%20apparently%20made%20during%20his%20four-day%20trip%20to%20China%2C%20shows%20him%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20seven%20states%20of%20India%2C%20the%20eastern%20part%20of%20India%2C%20are%20called%20the%20seven%20sisters.%20They%20are%20a%20landlocked%20region%20of%20India.%20They%20have%20no%20way%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20the%20ocean.%26quot%3B%20He%20says%20Bangladesh%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Bguardian%20of%20the%20ocean%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20region.%20%26quot%3BThis%20opens%20up%20a%20huge%20possibility.%20This%20could%20be%20an%20extension%20for%20the%20Chinese%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReacting%20to%20the%20remarks%2C%20Assam%20Chief%20Minister%20Himanta%20Biswa%20Sarma%20said%20what%20the%20Bangladesh%20leader%20had%20said%20was%20%26quot%3Boffensive%26quot%3B.%20He%20stressed%20the%20need%20to%20develop%20more%20robust%20rail%20and%20road%20networks%20connecting%20the%20Northeast%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20statement%20made%20by%20Md%20Younis%20of%20Bangladesh%20so%20called%20interim%20Government%20referring%20to%20the%20seven%20sister%20states%20of%20Northeast%20India%20as%20landlocked%20and%20positioning%20Bangladesh%20as%20their%20guardian%20of%20ocean%20access%2C%20is%20offensive%20and%20strongly%20condemnable.%20This%20remark%20underscores%20the%20persistent%20vulnerability%20narrative%20associated%20with%20India's%20strategic%20'Chicken's%20Neck'%20corridor.%26quot%3B%20The%20Chicken's%20Neck%20Corridor%20is%20a%20stretch%20of%20land%20in%20West%20Bengal's%20Siliguri%20which%20connects%20the%20region%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20India.%20Nepal%2C%20Bangladesh%20and%20Bhutan%20surround%20this%20stretch.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHistorically%2C%20even%20internal%20elements%20within%20India%20have%20dangerously%20suggested%20severing%20this%20critical%20passageway%20to%20isolate%20the%20Northeast%20from%20the%20mainland%20physically.%20Therefore%2C%20it%20is%20imperative%20to%20develop%20more%20robust%20railway%20and%20road%20networks%20both%20underneath%20and%20around%20the%20Chicken's%20Neck%20corridor.%20Additionally%2C%20exploring%20alternative%20road%20routes%20connecting%20the%20Northeast%20to%20mainland%20India%2C%20effectively%20bypassing%20the%20Chicken's%20Neck%2C%20should%20be%20prioritised%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Sarma%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThough%20this%20may%20pose%20significant%20engineering%20challenges%2C%20it%20is%20achievable%20with%20determination%20and%20innovation.%20Such%20provocative%20statements%20by%20Md%20Younis%20must%20not%20be%20taken%20lightly%2C%20as%20they%20reflect%20deeper%20strategic%20considerations%20and%20longstanding%20agendas%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20wrote%20to%20Mr%20Yunus%20on%20March%2026%2C%20wishing%20Bangladesh%20on%20its%20independence%20day.%20In%20his%20letter%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20highlighted%20the%20significance%20of%20mutual%20sensitivity%20and%20said%20the%20Bangladesh%20Liberation%20War%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bshared%20history%26quot%3B%20between%20the%20two%20countries.%20%26quot%3BWe%20remain%20committed%20to%20advancing%20this%20partnership%2C%20driven%20by%20our%20common%20aspirations%20for%20peace%2C%20stability%2C%20and%20prosperity%2C%20and%20based%20on%20mutual%20sensitivity%20to%20each%20other's%20interests%20and%20concerns%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743766200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2F5kf8m8b8_pm-mo