osed%20location%20in%20November.%3Cp%3ERussian%20Defense%20Ministry%20Press%20Service%20via%20AP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThere%20are%20so%20many%20drones%20over%20Ukraine%20that%20soldiers%20can%20be%20unsure%20which%20ones%20belong%20to%20each%20side.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20a%20Ukrainian%20operator%20said%20Russia%20is%20innovating%20less%2C%20making%20some%20of%20its%20drones%20easier%20to%20beat.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUkraine%20has%20hundreds%20of%20companies%20working%20on%20drones%2C%20while%20Russia%20has%20a%20more%20centralized%20approach.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20is%20flying%20fewer%20types%20of%20drones%20than%20Ukraine%2C%20which%20is%20making%20them%20easier%20to%20recognize%20and%20defeat%2C%20a%20Ukrainian%20drone%20operator%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDimko%20Zhluktenko%2C%20a%20drone%20operator%20with%20Ukraine's%20Unmanned%20Systems%20Forces%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukrainians-hunting-russian-drones-flying-double-barrel-recoilless-shotgun-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussian%20drone%3C%2Fa%3E%20types%2C%20%26quot%3Bit's%20very%20easy%20to%20identify%20them.%20They%20rarely%20make%20any%20changes%20to%20the%20design.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-did-russia-invade-ukraine-putin-politics-motive-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvasion%20of%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20become%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-ukraine-fights-russian-drones-with-truck-mounted-machine-gun-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20war%20of%20drone-filled%20skies%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20Ukraine%20is%20presenting%20a%20bigger%20variety%20of%20drone%20types%20to%20counter%2C%20aided%20by%20a%20huge%20domestic%20drone%20industry%20with%20hundreds%20of%20companies%20producing%20a%20vast%20range%20of%20different%20models%20and%20technologies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%2C%20in%20contrast%2C%20has%20focused%20on%20making%20bigger%20numbers%20of%20just%20a%20few%20models.%20While%20this%20has%20helped%20it%20produce%20them%20at%20scale%2C%20it%20also%20aids%20Ukrainian%20drone%20operators%20in%20identifying%20them%20and%20developing%20a%20sense%20of%20how%20to%20defeat%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d8fa79bd-097a-457b-b1c0-e2bafbab15a5%5C%22%3EHard%20to%20surprise%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EZhluktenko%20said%20that%20Ukraine's%20more%20dispersed%20way%20of%20making%20drones%20means%20that%20%26quot%3Bit%20is%20very%20hard%20for%20them%20to%20surprise%20us%20and%20it's%20very%20easy%20for%20us%20to%20surprise%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20Russia%20doesn't%20upgrade%20its%20drone%20designs%20very%20often%2C%20so%20it%20can%20be%20%26quot%3Bvery%20easy%20to%20identify%20friend%2Ffoe.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20defense%20procurement%20is%20highly%20centralized%2C%20with%20soldiers%20getting%20material%20through%20state%20weapons%20manufacturers%20and%20Russian%20allies%20like%20Iran%20and%20North%20Korea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%2C%20in%20contrast%2C%20has%20hundreds%20of%20homegrown%20defense%20companies%20that%20work%20directly%20with%20soldiers%20to%20develop%2C%20test%2C%20and%20roll%20out%20gear%2C%20as%20well%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgofundwar-ukraine-crowdfunding-battle-against-russia-defense-equipment-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evolunteer%20networks%20that%20buy%2C%20alter%2C%20and%20develop%20new%20equipment%20for%20soldiers%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20holding%20a%20drone%20in%20Donetsk%20Oblast%2C%20Ukraine%2C%20on%20February%2019%2C%202025.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67bc5573c832c3638fa4fe46%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20holding%20a%20drone%20in%20Donetsk%20Oblast%2C%20Ukraine.%3Cp%3EWolfgang%20Schwan%2FAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20Patton%20Rogers%2C%20a%20drone%20expert%20at%20the%20Cornell%20Brooks%20Tech%20Policy%20Institute%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20Russia's%20more%20centralized%20process%20means%20that%20%26quot%3Bif%20there's%20an%20error%20with%20a%20component%20part%2C%20then%20it%20will%20be%20an%20error%20that%20spreads%20across%20systems.%20If%20there's%20a%20loophole%20that%20allows%20you%20to%20hack%2C%20then%20it%20spreads%20across%20all%20systems%20and%20makes%20them%20vulnerable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20different%20varieties%20of%20drones%20give%20Ukraine%20some%20advantages%2C%20but%20it%20still%20has%20a%20huge%20challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20advisor%20to%20Ukrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2025%2F03%2F27%2Fnx-s1-5338557%2Fukraine-is-at-the-cutting-edge-of-drone-innovation-but-russia-is-catching-up%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSo%2520it%2527s%2520only%2520Ukrainian%2520soldiers%2Ccalls%2520it%2520a%2520technological%2520race.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20NPR%20last%20month%20that%20Russia%20is%20a%20few%20months%20behind%20Ukraine%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20drone%20innovation%2C%20but%20has%20a%20far%20larger%20production%20capacity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20production%20gap%20means%20Ukraine's%20soldiers%20are%20still%20using%20some%20drones%20bought%20from%20Western%20and%20Chinese%20companies.%20Those%20can%20be%20bought%20by%20the%20soldiers%20themselves%2C%20or%20by%20crowdfunding%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhluktenko%20said%20they%20are%20needed%2C%20but%20typically%20don't%20perform%20as%20well%20as%20Ukrainian-made%20drones%20designed%20specifically%20for%20this%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227a3b54c6-00d6-43a7-8383-60d296603388%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20booming%20drone%20industry%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20is%20making%20most%20of%20its%20drones%20itself.%20Its%20military%20said%20more%20than%2096%25%20of%20the%201.5%20million%20drones%20it%20bought%20last%20year%20were%20of%20Ukrainian%20origin%2C%20and%20that%20number%20is%20set%20to%20increase%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20said%20his%20country%20would%20make%201.4%20million%20drones%20in%202024%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20clear%20if%20that%20goal%20was%20met.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20drones%20that%20Russia%20has%20fired%20at%20Ukraine%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-level-up-shahed-drones-chinese-antenna-bypass-jammers-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20been%20Shaheds%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20type%20of%20drone%20given%20to%20Russia%20by%20Iran%20and%20that%20Russia%20has%20started%20making%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225993%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Ukrainian%20officer%20shows%20a%20thermobaric%20charge%20of%20a%20downed%20Shahed%20drone%20at%20an%20undisclosed%20location%20in%20Ukraine%20in%20November.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ef95ae5d203112923e11cf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223995%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20officer%20shows%20a%20thermobaric%20charge%20of%20a%20downed%20Shahed%20drone.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FEfrem%20Lukatsky%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMauro%20Gilli%2C%20a%20senior%20researcher%20in%20military%20technology%20at%20ETH%20Zurich%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20Russia%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20have%20the%20type%20of%20production%2C%20both%20scale%20and%20diversity%2C%20that%20Ukraine%20has.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20that%20Ukraine%20has%20been%20the%20first%20in%20the%20world%20to%20develop%20some%20drone%20tech.%20Ukraine's%20pioneering%20drone%20types%20have%20included%20different%20naval%20drones%2C%20and%20drones%20that%20can%20fly%20over%201%2C800%20miles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225927bd1a-ff55-4a8b-91d4-35bc5321ae90%5C%22%3EA%20drone%20war%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDrones%20remain%20key%20to%20Ukraine's%20fightback%20against%20Russia%2C%20especially%20given%20its%20smaller%20military%20and%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhluktenko%20said%20that%20in%20his%20unit's%20area%20of%20the%20front%2C%20up%20to%2080%25%20of%20hits%20on%20Russian%20infantry%20and%20mechanized%20targets%20are%20being%20made%20by%20drones.%20Ukraine%20also%20uses%20them%20to%20identify%20and%20launch%20attacks%2C%20hit%20Russian%20ships%20and%20oil%20refineries%2C%20and%20in%20place%20of%20weaponry%20like%20artillery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20Russia's%20approach%20to%20different%20drone%20models%20makes%20it%20easier%2C%20defeating%20them%20is%20still%20a%20struggle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhluktenko%20said%20it%20can%20still%20be%20%26quot%3Ba%20big%20problem%26quot%3B%20to%20recognize%20whose%20drones%20are%20whose%2C%20because%20there%20are%20so%20many%20flying%20at%20any%20given%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20drone%20operator%2C%20who%20spoke%20to%20BI%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity%2C%20said%20there%20can%20be%20so%20many%20drones%20in%20the%20sky%20that%20infantry%20can%20be%20ordered%20to%20shoot%20down%20every%20one%20they%20see.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20they%20said%20that%20Ukraine's%20overall%20tactics%20and%20equipment%20were%20constantly%20changing%20toward%20unmanned%20systems%2C%20and%20that%20drones%20were%20proving%20%26quot%3Bdecisive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20will%20be%20hoping%20it%20can%20keep%20this%20advantage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-flying-fewer-types-drones-over-ukraine-easier-to-target-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743765415000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ef964ab8b41a9673fca23b%3F