an%20regain%20control%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20workplace%20driven%20by%20fear%20and%20an%20idealized%20version%20of%20productivity%20won't%20necessarily%20deliver%20results%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20Homa%20Bahrami%2C%20a%20senior%20lecturer%20at%20the%20Haas%20School%20of%20Business%20of%20UC%20Berkeley%2C%20said%20that%20while%20workers%20may%20comply%20in%20the%20short%20run%20when%20CEOs%20put%20a%20virtual%20%26quot%3Bgun%20to%20their%20head%2C%26quot%3B%20such%20moves%20would%20impact%20goodwill%2C%20commitment%2C%20and%20the%20emotional%20engagement%20of%20the%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUltimately%2C%20if%20you're%20working%20in%20a%20place%20with%20core%20values%20are%20exactly%20the%20opposite%20of%20yours%20as%20a%20human%20being%2C%20then%20it's%20not%20sustainable%2C%20and%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20make%20it%20really%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Bahrami.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEurich%20also%20echoed%20this%20sentiment%20and%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-damage-gen-z-careers-tech-layoffs-job-market-hiring-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaying%20off%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20set%20an%20example%20the%20%26quot%3Bmost%20counterproductive%20thing%26quot%3B%20a%20company%20could%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20ways%20for%20workers%20to%20push%20back%20and%20regain%20some%20extent%20of%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBahrami%20said%20that%20though%20burnout%20can%20often%20not%20be%20avoided%20when%20conditions%20are%20adverse%2C%20it%20helps%20to%20have%20a%20forward-looking%20mindset%2C%20update%20skills%20proactively%2C%20and%20set%20goals%20for%20reaching%20an%20ideal%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarfoush%20said%20that%20even%20small%20acts%20of%20resistance%20could%20go%20a%20long%20way%2C%20starting%20with%20delaying%20that%20first%20email%20check%20until%20an%20hour%20after%20waking%20up%2C%20taking%20real%20lunch%20breaks%2C%20and%2C%20for%20managers%2C%20having%20expl