20bans%20against%20the%20use%20of%20weapons%20like%20land%20mines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b5fe0d7b-6614-4a8e-bc6f-187ada27d644%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELand%20mines%20make%20a%20comeback%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFinland%20will%20prepare%20for%20the%20withdrawal%20from%20the%20Ottawa%20Convention%2C%26quot%3B%20Finnish%20President%20Alexander%20Stubb%20posted%20on%20X%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20decision%20was%20%26quot%3Bbased%20on%20a%20thorough%20assessment%20by%20the%20relevant%20ministries%20and%20the%20Defence%20Forces%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20added%20that%20the%20country%20was%20%26quot%3Bcommitted%20to%20its%20international%20obligations%20on%20the%20responsible%20use%20of%20mines.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Ottawa%20Convention%20has%20over%20160%20signatories%2C%20with%20the%20US%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20China%20among%20the%20notable%20absences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20announcing%20their%20own%20decision%2C%20Estonia%2C%20Latvia%2C%20Lithuania%2C%20and%20Poland%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20that%20in%20the%20current%20security%20environment%2C%20it%20is%20of%20paramount%20importance%20to%20provide%20our%20defense%20forces%20with%20flexibility%20and%20freedom%20of%20choice%20of%20potential%20use%20of%20new%20weapon%20systems%20and%20solutions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Landmine%20Ukraine%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ef9599b8b41a9673fca230%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20piling%20unexploded%20land%20mines%20in%20a%20hole%20to%20be%20destroyed%20in%202023.%3Cp%3EChris%20McGrath%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20NATO%20members%20have%20developed%20tactics%20based%20on%20the%20assumption%20that%20modern%20armies%20would%20have%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-kursk-shows-ability-without-much-west-advice-former-nato-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20to%20be%20highly%20maneuverable.%3C%2Fa%3E%20But%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20has%20come%20to%20more%20resemble%20World%20War%20I%2C%20with%20sides%20entrenched%20in%20heavily%20defended%20static%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEuropean%20countries%20now%20seem%20to%20be%20rapidly%20adjusting%20their%20strategies%20in%20response%20to%20the%20lessons%20from%20Ukraine%2C%20and%20over%20fears%20that%20Russia%20could%20attack%20elsewhere%20in%20Europe%20if%20it%20gets%20a%20partial%20victory%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJacob%20Parakilas%2C%20a%20research%20leader%20for%20Defence%20Strategy%2C%20Policy%20and%20Capabilities%20at%20RAND%20Europe%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20had%20proven%20the%20continued%20utility%20of%20land%20mines.%20%26quot%3BThe%20landmine%20still%20has%20significant%20military%20value%20in%20shaping%20the%20battlefield%20and%20deterring%20or%20slowing%20enemy%20advances%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2298cb26ba-0d45-4af0-b7f9-e46821345cce%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMines%2C%20Mines%2C%20everywhere%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Ukraine%2C%20both%20sides%20have%20often%20struggled%20to%20break%20through%20each%20other's%20defensive%20positions%2C%20some%20of%20which%20are%20heavily%20fortified%20with%20minefields.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-the-ukrainian-counteroffensive-ran-into-trouble-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUkraine's%202023%20counteroffensive%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Russia%20laid%20vast%20swaths%20of%20the%20explosives%2C%20and%20Ukraine%20has%20also%20used%20land%20mines.%20Ukraine%20is%20now%20recognized%20as%20the%20most%20heavily%20mined%20country%20in%20the%20world%2C%20with%20estimates%20suggesting%20it%20could%20take%20decades%20and%20billions%20of%20dollars%20to%20neutralize%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENaval%20mines%20have%20also%20been%20deployed%20in%20the%20Black%20Sea%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblack-sea-naval-mine-clearance-ukraine-war-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhich%20offer%20their%20own%20issues%20and%20long-term%20challenges%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20land%20mines%2C%20Riccardo%20Labianco%2C%20the%20international%20policy%20manager%20at%20UK%20anti-landmines%20charity%20MAG%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20risk%20to%20civilians%20is%20too%20severe%20to%20justify%20abandoning%20the%20Ottawa%20Treaty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20recognize%20there%20are%20no%20easy%20choices%20when%20a%20state%20feels%20under%20threat%20of%20armed%20aggression%2C%20but%20International%20Humanitarian%20Law%2C%20including%20the%20Ottawa%20Convention%2C%20is%20designed%20precisely%20for%20times%20like%20these%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Marcus%20Solarz%20Hendriks%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20national%20security%20unit%20at%20Policy%20Exchange%2C%20co-authored%20a%20report%20last%20month%20calling%20for%20the%20UK%20government%20to%20abandon%20its%20own%20ban.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20BI%20that%20Ukraine%20had%20shown%20they%20were%20a%20vital%20weapon%20for%20defending%20against%20large-scale%20invasions%2C%20%26quot%3Bnamely%20by%20restricting%20maneuverability%20and%20channelizing%20troops%20into%20pre-prepared%20kill%20zones%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20areas%20where%20large%20gatherings%20of%20troops%20are%20targeted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20operational%20advantage%20is%20particularly%20well%20suited%20to%20numerically%20disadvantaged%20forces%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bas%20would%20likely%20be%20the%20case%20should%20these%20states%20be%20forced%20to%20defend%20against%20attempted%20Russian%20advances.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2207c2eb79-ae83-4c82-9f4b-4b90cf8fced5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGetting%20your%20hands%20on%20mines%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECountries%20like%20Finland%2C%20and%20to%20a%20lesser%20extent%20Latvia%20and%20Estonia%2C%20share%20long%20land%20borders%20with%20Russia%2C%20putting%20them%20on%20the%20frontline%20of%20any%20future%20Russian%20aggression.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinland%20also%20announced%20Tuesday%20it%20was%20increasing%20its%20defense%20budget%20to%203%25%20of%20GDP%2C%20and%20many%20nations%20bordering%20Russia%20are%20steeply%20increasing%20their%20defense%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20considering%20land%20mines%2C%20one%20issue%20could%20be%20obtaining%20them.%20The%20Ottawa%20Treaty%20bans%20not%20just%20the%20use%2C%20but%20also%20the%20manufacture%20of%20landmines%2C%20meaning%20they%20can't%20be%20easily%20bought%20on%20the%20European%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParakilas%20said%20that%20some%20European%20countries%20obtain%20mines%20from%20Singapore%20or%20South%20Korea%2C%20which%20has%20a%20large%2C%20heavily%20mined%20border%20zone%20with%20North%20Korea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20mines%20aren't%20difficult%20to%20make%2C%20he%20said%2C%20meaning%20that%20domestic%20production%20could%20be%20geared%20up%20in%20%26quot%3Bthe%20order%20of%20months%2C%20rather%20than%20years%20or%20decades.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20land%20mines%2C%20at%20their%20core%2C%20are%20little%20changed%2C%20some%20of%20the%20tech%20has%20developed.%20This%20includes%20sensors%20that%20enable%20mines%20Russia%20claims%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newscientist.com%2Farticle%2F2314453-russia-claims-smart-landmines-used-in-ukraine-only-target-soldiers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20have%20developed%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20distinguish%20between%20types%20of%20object%2C%20enabling%20them%20to%20tell%20apart%20an%20approaching%20civilian%20bus%20from%20a%20tank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20are%20fitted%20with%20devices%20that%20mean%20they%20defuse%20after%20a%20period%20of%20time%2C%20reducing%20the%20risk%20of%20civilians%20triggering%20forgotten%20but%20unexploded%20mines%20years%20l