.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Frise-in-incidents-of-hindu-temples-being-defaced-with-anti-india-graffiti-in-us-mea-tells-lok-sabha%2Farticleshow%2F119976312.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20has%20expressed%20serious%20concerns%20over%20the%20increasing%20incidents%20of%20anti-India%20graffiti%20defacing%20Hindu%20temples%20in%20the%20US.%20Diplomatic%20channels%20are%20actively%20addressing%20these%20hate%20crimes%2C%20with%20US%20authorities%20investigating%20and%20treating%20them%20as%20severe%20offenses.%20Members%20of%20US%20Congress%20have%20also%20advocated%20for%20broader%20strategies%20to%20counteract%20these%20hate%20crimes%20against%20Hindus.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Frise-in-incidents-of-hindu-temples-being-defaced-with-anti-india-graffiti-in-us-mea-tells-lok-sabha%2Farticleshow%2F119976312.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Delusion%20Is%20Dangerous%3A%20What%20Bangladesh%20And%20Yunus%20Must%20Understand%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EMohammad%20Yunus%2C%20the%20Nobel%20Prize%20winner%2C%20was%20in%20China%20recently%2C%20and%20in%20an%20exercise%20best%20characterised%20as%20one%20of%20supreme%20oratory%20acrobatics%2C%20he%20wove%20Northeast%20India%20into%20a%20narrative%20that%20reduces%20Bangladesh%20to%20the%20exclusive%20guardian%20of%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal.%20If%20this%20was%20a%20geopolitical%20chess%20move%2C%20it%20was%20one%20made%20with%20an%20aura%20of%20reckless%20irony%E2%80%94one%20that%20not%20only%20distorts%20reality%20but%20also%20threatens%20to%20inflame%20an%20already%20sensitive%20relationship%20with%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Laureate's%20Foray%20Into%20Grandstanding%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20China%2C%20a%20nation%20that%20has%20turned%20playing%20the%20power%20broker%20in%20South%20Asia%20into%20an%20art%20form%2C%20Yunus%20decided%20to%20go%20lyrical%20about%20how%20strategically%20significant%20Bangladesh%20is%2C%20labelling%20it%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bonly%20guardian%20of%20the%20sea%26quot%3B%20in%20South%20Asia.%20This%20would%20be%20funny%20if%20not%20so%20dishonest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20impossible%20not%20to%20be%20impressed%20by%20the%20sheer%20audacity%20of%20such%20a%20statement.%20To%20say%20that%20Bangladesh%2C%20which%20has%20710%20kilometres%20of%20coastline%2C%20is%20the%20sole%20guardian%20of%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal%20is%20to%20assert%20that%20Monaco%20is%20the%20absolute%20monarch%20of%20the%20Mediterranean.%20If%20this%20were%20just%20nationalist%20bombast%2C%20it%20could%20be%20safely%20ignored%20as%20empty%20posturing.%20But%20Yunus%20went%20beyond%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20sleight%20of%20hand%20that%20would%20shame%20an%20experienced%20magician%2C%20he%20brought%20India's%20Northeast%20into%20the%20story%2C%20the%20implied%20suggestion%20being%20that%20the%20access%20to%20the%20sea%20for%20the%20region%20lies%20at%20the%20whim%20of%20Dhaka.%20Naturally%2C%20this%20completely%20ignores%20India's%20own%20deep-sea%20ports%2C%20its%20burgeoning%20maritime%20strength%2C%20and%20its%20historically%20ancient%20trade%20routes.%20But%20why%20let%20facts%20spoil%20a%20good%20diplomatic%20play%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Northeast%3A%20A%20Convenient%20Pawn%20in%20the%20Narrative%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20something%20richly%20symbolic%20about%20Yunus's%20bid%20to%20make%20Bangladesh%20the%20exclusive%20gateway%20between%20the%20Indian%20Northeast%20and%20the%20world%20economy.%20He%20demonstrated%20that%20infatuation%20in%20Paris%2C%20even%20a%20few%20days%20before%20he%20took%20charge%20of%20the%20beleaguered%20country.%20The%20Northeast%2C%20with%20its%20convoluted%20topography%20and%20sensibilities%20forged%20in%20history%2C%20has%20been%20a%20place%20of%20intrigue%20and%20contest%20for%20centuries.%20But%20any%20suggestion%20that%20India's%20Northeast%20has%20no%20access%20to%20the%20sea%20except%20through%20Bangladesh%20is%20not%20only%20erroneous%E2%80%94it%20is%20an%20outright%20fabrication.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20been%20heavily%20investing%20in%20its%20own%20maritime%20infrastructure.%20The%20Sittwe%20Port%20in%20Myanmar%2C%20which%20was%20built%20under%20India's%20Kaladan%20Multi-Modal%20Transit%20Transport%20Project%2C%20is%20a%20clear%20indication%20of%20India's%20attempts%20to%20decrease%20dependence%20on%20Bangladesh%20for%20sea%20access.%20In%20addition%2C%20the%20Northeast%20is%20well-linked%20to%20Kolkata%20and%20other%20ports%20through%20extensive%20road%20and%20rail%20networks%2C%20with%20projects%20currently%20underway%20to%20further%20improve%20connectivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Yunus's%20claim%20does%20have%20a%20specific%20agenda%3A%20it%20adds%20fuel%20to%20Dhaka's%20increasing%20narrative%20that%20the%20key%20to%20regional%20trade%20lies%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20conveniently%20overlooking%20India's%20long%20strategic%20options.%20This%20is%20not%20merely%20a%20naive%20mistake%E2%80%94it%20is%20a%20deliberate%20attempt%20to%20make%20Bangladesh%20geopolitically%20relevant%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20truth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Love-Hate%20Relationship%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20there's%20one%20nation%20that%20has%20gone%20to%20great%20lengths%20to%20appease%20Bangladesh's%20ascension%2C%20it%20is%20India.%20From%20underwriting%20Bangladesh's%20independence%20in%201971%20to%20giving%20preferential%20trade%20concessions%2C%20India%20has%20been%20a%20regional%20stabilising%20influence%20throughout.%20The%20surrender%20of%20Pakistan's%2093%2C000%20soldiers%20to%20the%20Indian%20Army%20at%20Dhaka%20in%201971%20came%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20about%203%2C000%20Indian%20soldiers'%20lives.%20But%20more%20often%20than%20not%2C%20Dhaka's%20political%20leaders%20and%2C%20these%20days%2C%20even%20many%20of%20its%20intellectuals%2C%20seem%20to%20have%20an%20almost%20stereotypical%20compulsion%20to%20provoke%20the%20bear.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20question%20that%20Bangladesh%20has%20gone%20a%20long%20way%20in%20economic%20development%20and%20progress%2C%20surpassing%20India%20in%20many%20human%20development%20indices%2C%20but%20its%20habit%20of%20playing%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20geopolitical%20fence%E2%80%94courting%20Beijing%20even%20as%20it%20attempts%20friendly%20relations%20with%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%94has%20tended%20to%20border%20on%20reckless%20opportunism.%20Bangladesh's%20increasing%20economic%20ties%20with%20China%2C%20such%20as%20the%20growing%20dependence%20on%20Chinese%20investments%20in%20strategic%20infrastructure%2C%20have%20not%20escaped%20India's%20notice.%20But%20for%20a%20public%20icon%20like%20Yunus%20to%20utilise%20China%20as%20a%20platform%20for%20undermining%20India's%20stand%20in%20the%20region%20is%20a%20whole%20different%20level%20of%20misreading.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EChina%3A%20The%20Convenient%20Audience%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20should%20be%20no%20surprise%2C%20therefore%2C%20that%20Yunus%20decided%20on%20China%20as%20the%20arena%20of%20his%20statements.%20Beijing%20long%20desired%20to%20reinforce%20its%20footprint%20within%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal%20by%20using%20Bangladesh%20as%20a%20willing%20accomplice%20in%20its%20Belt%20and%20Road%20Initiative%20(BRI).%20By%20blowing%20a%20whistle%20loudly%20that%20Bangladesh%20is%20China's%20predominant%20seagoing%20entryway%20for%20the%20region%2C%20Yunus%20unwittingly%20(or%20probably%20with%20motive)%20echoes%20the%20stated%20aspirations%20of%20Beijing%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%2C%20naturally%2C%20greets%20such%20stories%20with%20alacrity.%20For%20years%2C%20it%20has%20been%20trying%20to%20chip%20away%20at%20India's%20regional%20dominance%2C%20and%20having%20their%20neighbour's%20star%20%E2%80%98leaders'%20play%20into%20its%20hands%20is%20the%20ultimate%20fantasy.%20The%20question%20is%2C%20however%2C%20whether%20Dhaka%20fully%20appreciates%20the%20fallout%20of%20such%20grandstanding.%20Playing%20the%20China%20card%20may%20be%20a%20shrewd%20diplomatic%20move%2C%20but%20one%20that%20is%20accompanied%20by%20strings%E2%80%94strings%20that%20have%20a%20habit%20of%20turning%20into%20nightmares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Real%20Guardian%20Of%20The%20Bay%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20all%20of%20Yunus's%20bombastic%20rhetoric%2C%20reality%20is%20harshly%20different.%20India's%20Andaman%20and%20Nicobar%20Command%20is%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal's%20principal%20military%20base%2C%20and%20India's%20navy%20commands%20the%20most%20assertive%20maritime%20presence%20there.%20The%20country's%20sea%20trade%20routes%2C%20naval%20patrols%2C%20and%20disaster%20relief%20arrangements%20are%20primarily%20powered%20by%20Indian%20strength%2C%20rather%20than%20Dhaka's%20good%20wishes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20commerce%20and%20trade%2C%20Bangladesh%20is%20not%20the%20sole%20gatekeeper%20Yunus%20assumes%20it%20to%20be.%20The%20Bay%20of%20Bengal%20Initiative%20for%20Multi-Sectoral%20Technical%20and%20Economic%20Cooperation%20(BIMSTEC)%2C%20an%20alliance%20that%20involves%20India%2C%20Myanmar%2C%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20Thailand%2C%20among%20others%2C%20guarantees%20that%20one%20country%20does%20not%20have%20complete%20dominance%20over%20regional%20sea%20affairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Dhaka%20thinks%20it%20is%20the%20only%20custodian%20of%20the%20sea%2C%20it%20might%20have%20to%20go%20back%20to%20the%20very%20basics%20of%20regional%20geopolitics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAdding%20Fuel%20To%20The%20Fire%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20time%20when%20India%20and%20Bangladesh%20are%20struggling%20to%20resolve%20sensitive%20issues%20such%20as%20the%20Teesta%20water-sharing%20dispute%2C%20cross-border%20trade%20imbalances%2C%20and%20the%20Rohingya%20crisis%2C%20etc%2C%20Yunus's%20statement%20helps%20little%20to%20promote%20goodwill.%20Rather%2C%20they%20introduce%20an%20extra%20layer%20of%20tension%20into%20a%20relationship%20already%20characterised%20by%20cautious%20diplomacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENew%20Delhi%20has%20thus%20far%20been%20indulgent%20towards%20Bangladesh's%20flirtations%20with%20Beijing%2C%20aware%20of%20the%20economic%20compulsions%20that%20dictate%20Dhaka's%20decisions.%20But%20indulgence%20has%20its%20limits.%20If%20personalities%20as%20powerful%20as%20Yunus%20start%20to%20amplify%20stories%20that%20attempt%20to%20downplay%20India's%20role%20in%20the%20region%20and%20exaggerate%20Bangladesh's%20bargaining%20power%2C%20Dhaka%20will%20not%20be%20long%20in%20facing%20a%20much%20less%20indulgent%20neighbour.%20History%20has%20repeatedly%20demonstrated%20that%20driving%20India%20into%20a%20defensive%20position%20seldom%20works%20out%20well%20for%20its%20smaller%20neighbours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPride%20vs%20Overreach%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20Bangladesh%20asserting%20itself%20in%20the%20world.%20Indeed%2C%20its%20economic%20development%2C%20despite%20its%20inbuilt%20challenges%20and%20strategic%20value%2C%20should%20be%20recognised%20and%20respected.%20But%20there%20is%20a%20thin%20line%20between%20national%20pride%20and%20strategic%20overreach.%20Announcing%20oneself%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bonly%20guardian%20of%20the%20sea%26quot%3B%20while%20quietly%20undermining%20the%20region's%20greatest%20power%20is%20not%20only%20overreach%E2%80%94it%20is%20diplomatic%20hubris.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYunus%2C%20in%20his%20history%20of%20advocating%20microfinance%20and%20social%20enterprise%2C%20would%20do%20well%20to%20keep%20in%20mind%20that%20credibility%2C%20just%20like%20goodwill%2C%20is%20earned%20hard%20but%20lost%20with%20ease.%20A%20Nobel%20Prize%20confers%20no%20immunity%20from%20geopolitical%20fact%2C%20nor%20does%20a%20passionate%20address%20in%20Beijing%20turn%20the%20tides%20of%20power%20in%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal.%20The%20sea%20does%20not%20bow%20to%20words%2C%20and%20neither%20does%20the%20region's%20balance%20of%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(The%20writer%2C%20a%20senior%20social%20sector%20leader%2C%20can%20be%20reached%20at%20mbiswanath%40gmail.com.%20The%20opinion%20expressed%20here%20is%20his%20own.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743760380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2F8g7ufbe_yunus-xi-_625x300_28_March_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fdelusion-is-dangerous-what-bangladesh-and-yunus-need-to-understand-about-india-and-northeast-8085707%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22To%20say%20that%20Bangladesh%2C%20which%20has%20710%20kilometres%20of%20coastline%2C%20is%20the%20sole%20guardian%20of%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal%20is%20to%20assert%20that%20Monaco%20is%20the%20absolute%20monarch%20of%20the%20Mediterranean.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Clio%20Barnard%20Sets%20Next%20Feature%20%E2%80%98I%20See%20Buildings%20Fall%20Like%20Lightning%2C%E2%80%99%20Anthony%20Boyle%2C%20Joe%20Cole%2C%20Jay%20Lycurgo%2C%20Daryl%20McCormack%20and%20Lola%20Petticrew%20to%20Star%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743760360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F04%2FI-SEE-BUILDINGS-FALL-LIKE-LIGHTNING-First-Look.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236359784%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Clio%20Barnard%2C%20the%20BAFTA-nominated%20writer%2Fdirector%20behind%20acclaimed%20British%20indie%20films%20such%20as%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Selfish%20Giant%2C%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CDark%20River%E2%80%9D%20an