0Studio%20Ghibli-style%20images%20being%20churned%20out%20by%20OpenAI's%20new%20ChatGPT%20Image%20Generator.%20Altman's%20words%20struck%20me%20as%20deeply%20ironic%20%E2%80%94%20the%20whole%20point%20of%20AI%20art%2C%20as%20its%20proponents%20keep%20reminding%20us%2C%20is%20that%20sleepless%20nights%20are%20not%20required%20to%20create%20these%20images.%20Users%20worldwide%20currently%20%E2%80%98Ghiblifying'%20their%20personal%20photographs%20aren't%20losing%20any%20sleep.%20The%20only%20people%20involved%20in%20this%20situation%20who've%20spent%20sleepless%20nights%20creating%20art%20are%20Studio%20Ghibli's%20Hayao%20Miyazaki%20and%20his%20team%20of%20artists%2C%20animators%2C%20et%20al.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20people%20currently%20being%20ripped%20off%20by%20half%20the%20planet%20because%20in%202023%2C%20the%20Japanese%20government%20declared%20that%20copyrighted%20works%20could%20be%20used%2C%20sans%20permission%2C%20for%20AI-training%20endeavors%20(a%20position%20that%20the%20US%2C%20the%20UK%20and%20the%20EU%20are%20still%20distant%20from%2C%20legally%20speaking).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20Theft%20Is%20Art%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ongoing%20Studio%20Ghibli%20situation%20really%20is%20the%20perfect%20distillation%20of%20AI%20art%20discourse%E2%80%94an%20act%20of%20material%20theft%20and%20creative%20bankruptcy%20is%20being%20paraded%20as%20pathbreaking%20innovation.%20And%20you're%20being%20asked%20to%20shift%20your%20gaze%20from%20the%20scene%20of%20the%20crime%20and%20focus%20instead%20on%20the%20genteel%20faces%20and%20kind%20eyes%20of%20Studio%20Ghibli%20grandmas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20my%20mind%2C%20there%20are%20three%20principal%20aspects%20of%20the%20AI%20art%20debate%3A%20material%20(pertaining%20to%20the%20labour-capital%20relationship%20between%20artists%20and%20corporations)%2C%20legal%20(pertaining%20to%20the%20ownership%2Fdistribution%20of%20art)%20and%20aesthetic%20(pertaining%20to%20inherent%20artistic%20value).%20And%20on%20all%20three%20planks%2C%20generative%20AI%E2%80%94at%20least%20in%20its%20current%20shape%20and%20form%2C%20exemplified%20by%20OpenAI's%20ChatGPT%E2%80%94seems%20to%20me%20to%20be%20a%20net%20negative%20for%20humanity%20in%20general%2C%20and%20a%20crushing%20blow%20in%20particular%20to%20artists%20and%20creators%20everywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EManufacturing%20Consent%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20the%20material%20aspect.%20Let's%20say%20you%20are%20a%20freelance%20artist%20and%20designer%20who%20was%20commissioned%20to%20create%20a%20few%20minor%20logos%20and%20webpages%20for%20a%20mega-corporation%2C%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20ago.%20At%20the%20completion%20of%20said%20project%2C%20you%20were%20paid%20what%20you%20assumed%20was%20a%20fair%20wage.%20But%20now%2C%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20later%2C%20you%20realise%20that%20the%20mega-corporation%20is%20also%20deeply%20invested%20in%20AI%2C%20and%20has%20been%20feeding%20all%20of%20your%20work%20(not%20just%20the%20finished%20product%2C%20but%20stage-updates%20and%20mockups%20as%20well)%20into%20the%20data-guzzling%2C%20AI-training%20machine.%20You%20never%20consented%20to%20this%20process%2C%20but%20your%20consent%20may%20have%20been%20manufactured%20by%20vaguely-phrased%20clauses%20buried%20deep%20within%20your%20standard-issue%20freelancer's%20contract.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20way%2C%20the%20mega-corporation%20gets%20to%20use%20your%20work%20twice%3A%20once%20in%20the%20usual%20way%2C%20and%20then%20once%20more%20for%20AI-training.%20The%20mega-corporation%20gets%20two%20bites%20at%20the%20apple%20but%20has%20to%20pay%20only%20for%20the%20first%20one.%20This%20is%20theft%20in%20the%20most%20ab%20initio%2C%20first%20principles%20sort%20of%20way.%20Every%20day%20is%20a%20cost-cutting%20day%20if%20you%20can%20simply%20get%20free%20work%20off%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Copyright%20Loophole%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20aspect%20speaks%20to%20legalities%2C%20which%20in%20this%20case%20means%20the%20concept%20of%20copyright.%20For%20successive%20decades%2C%20large%20corporations%20told%20us%20that%20copyright%20law%20was%20sacrosanct%2C%20that%20without%20the%20legal%20protections%20that%20controlled%20access%2C%20writers%20and%20artists%20and%20creators%20everywhere%20would%20be%20impoverished.%20You%20might%20remember%20the%20tragic%20suicide%20of%20Aaron%20Swartz%20(1986-2013)%2C%20the%20genius%20programmer%20behind%20the%20RSS%20web%20feed%20format%20and%20the%20development%20of%20Reddit.%20Swartz%20was%20threatened%20with%2050-plus%20years%20in%20prison%20for%20downloading%20a%20stash%20of%20JSTOR%20articles%20(JSTOR%20is%20a%20repository%20of%20paywalled%20academic%20articles)%20off%20MIT%20servers%2C%20which%20prompted%20him%20to%20take%20his%20own%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20now%2C%20we%20are%20suddenly%20being%20told%20by%20Altman%20and%20co.%20that%20unless%20we%20suspend%20the%20idea%20of%20copyright%20completely%20and%20allow%20copyrighted%20works%20to%20be%20chewed%20up%20by%20AI-training%20ventures%2C%20we%20are%20being%20anti-progress%20and%20undemocratic.%20It's%20funny%20how%20ideas%20of%20progress%2C%20fairness%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgreater%20good%E2%80%9D%20seem%20to%20gravitate%20around%20the%20interests%20of%20billionaires%2C%20shifting%20one%20way%20and%20then%20another%20in%20sync%20with%20share%20prices%20and%20investor%20valuations.%20Why%20should%20independent%20artists%20and%20creators%20embrace%20a%20technology%20and%20an%20extra-legal%20framework%20explicitly%20designed%20to%20undercut%20and%20eventually%20replace%20them%3F%20In%202024%2C%20Mira%20Murati%2C%20then-CEO%20of%20OpenAI%2C%20said%20that%20AI%20will%20definitely%20replace%20some%20creative%20jobs%20but%20that%20it%20was%20alright%20because%20%E2%80%9Cmaybe%20those%20creative%20jobs%20shouldn't%20have%20existed%20in%20the%20first%20place%E2%80%9D.%20In%20the%20%E2%80%98growth-hack'%20model%20of%20the%20universe%20favoured%20by%20Silicon%20Valley%20executives%20like%20Murati%2C%20creativity%20is%20an%20active%20threat%20that%20can%20and%20should%20be%20snuffed%20out%20by%20machine%20logic%2C%20the%20imperceptible%20hum%20of%20digital%20ones%20and%20zeroes.%20No%20surprise%20then%2C%20that%20influential%20groups%20of%20creators%20worldwide%20are%20suing%20OpenAI%20and%20co.%20for%20copyright%20infringement%E2%80%94the%20comedian%20Sarah%20Silverman%20is%20leading%20one%20such%20lawsuit%20against%20Meta%2C%20for%20example%2C%20while%20%3Cem%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20its%20own%20lawsuit%20against%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EArt%20Minus%20The%20Artist%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20aspect%20of%20the%20situation%20speaks%20to%20the%20purely%20aesthetic%2C%20the%20raw%20artistic%20value%20(if%20any)%20of%20AI-generated%20imagery.%20Every%20single%20professional%20artist%20I%20have%20spoken%20to%20or%20heard%20online%20testifies%20to%20how%20terrible%2C%20soulless%20and%20emotionally%20hollow%20AI-generated%20art%20is.%20Quite%20simply%2C%20the%20tech%20simply%20isn't%20very%20good.%20How%20could%20it%20be%20any%20good%2C%20when%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20culturally%20significant%20art%20is%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20still%20protected%20by%20copyright%20law%3F%20Existing%20image%20generators%20are%20being%20trained%20on%20leftovers%2C%20discards%20and%20amateur%2Flearner%20fare%2C%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20with%20Japan%20being%20a%20rogue%20exception%2C%20of%20course%2C%20thanks%20to%20its%20whimsical%20interpretation%20of%20copyright.%20For%20professional%20artists%2C%20the%20most%20common%20ongoing%20use%20case%20is%20to%20create%20mockups%20or%20demos%20for%20prospective%20clients%E2%80%94demonstrating%20what%20a%20particular%20style%20or%20color%20palette%20might%20plausibly%20look%20like.%20And%20even%20there%2C%20as%20professionals%20would%20know%2C%20there%20are%20significant%20limitations%20to%20the%20output.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20why%20AI-generated%20art%20is%20so%20terrible%20brings%20us%20to%20an%20intangible%20fourth%20aspect%20of%20the%20situation%3A%20the%20philosophical.%20Think%20about%20the%20very%20concept%20of%20image%20generators%20for%20a%20minute%E2%80%94they%20seek%2C%20essentially%2C%20to%20conjure%20art%20out%20of%20thin%20air%20while%20completely%20isolating%20the%20(ChatGPT)%20user%20from%20the%20process.%20An%20artefact%20minus%20the%20artistry.%20A%20hunk%20of%20butter%20that's%20all%20hunk%20and%20no%20butter%20is%20futile%2C%20both%20nutritionally%20and%20ontologically.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20artist's%20work%2C%20especially%20when%20it's%20beyond%20a%20certain%20minimum%20quality%2C%20speaks%20to%20their%20very%20soul%2C%20the%20story%20of%20their%20life.%20And%20the%20story%20is%20ingrained%20upon%20their%20callused%20hands%2C%20like%20a%20grand%20old%20tree%20marking%20the%20passage%20of%20every%20solar%20cycle%20with%20a%20concentric%20ring.%20To%20remove%20the%20process%20of%20learning%20your%20craft%2C%20to%20remove%20the%20inevitable%20sequence%20of%20mistake-correction-growth%20from%20an%20artist's%20life%2C%20is%20downright%20dystopian%20and%20a%20fundamentally%20antagonistic%20attitude%20towards%20art%20and%20artists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20Insult%2C%20Indeed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBack%20in%202016%2C%20Hayao%20Miyazaki%20himself%20was%20given%20a%20brief%20demonstration%20of%20AI-based%20animation%20techniques%2C%20and%20it%20left%20the%20veteran%20animator%20and%20filmmaker%20unimpressed%2C%20even%20shaken.%20The%20phrase%20he%20used%20to%20describe%20the%20experience%20was%20%E2%80%9Can%20insult%20to%20life%20itself%E2%80%9D.%20I%20think%20he%20was%20absolutely%20right.%20If%20you're%20currently%20getting%20a%20chuckle%20out%20of%20%E2%80%98Ghiblifying'%20your%20last%20year's%20Himachal%20road-trip%2C%20I'd%20urge%20you%20to%20listen%20to%20the%20man%20responsible%20for%20those%20genteel%20faces%20and%20kind%20eyes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Aditya%20Mani%20Jha%20is%20an%20independent%20writer%20living%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20His%20first%20work%20of%20nonfiction%20will%20be%20published%20by%20Oxford%20University%20Press%20in%202025)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743752160000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2F2sjbdtto_ghibli_625x300_04_April_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwhy-does-your-ai-ghibli-look-so-terrible-because-it-is-8084698%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22What%20happens%20when%20AI%20conjures%20art%20out%20of%20thin%20air%20while%20completely%20isolating%20the%20user%20from%20the%20process%3F%20You%20get%20what%20is%2C%20essentially%2C%20just%20an%20artefact%2C%20minus%20the%20artistry.%20A%20hunk%20of%20butter%20that's%20all%20hunk%20and%20no%20butter.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwhy-does-your-ai-ghibli-look-so-terrible-because-it-is-8084698%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22LIC%20rejects%20USTR's%20claim%20of%20having%20unfair%20advantage%20as%20state-owned%20firm%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743752054000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Flic-refutes-ustr-claims-denies-invoking-sovereign-guarantee-on-policies-125040400528_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sovereign%20guarantee%20has%20never%20been%20used%20as%20a%20marketing%20tool%20for%20policies%2C%20says%20company%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Flic-refutes-ustr-claims-denies-invoking-sovereign-guarantee-on-policies-125040400528_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%