les%2Fc1k4em2yz9eo%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc1k4em2yz9eo.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc1k4em2yz9eo.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Banana%20War%20To%20Trump%20Tariffs%2C%20A%20Brief%20History%20Of%20Trade%20Wars%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ERoughly%2019%20minutes%20into%20his%20speech%2C%20Trump%20was%20handed%20a%20rectangular%20board%20with%20a%20list%20of%20countries%20and%20regions%20and%20the%20tariffs%20they%20charged%20on%20America.%20Also%20mentioned%20were%20the%20reciprocal%20tariffs%20the%20US%20would%20charge%20henceforth.%20But%20it%20wasn't%20the%20first%20time%20a%20country%20took%20such%20a%20measure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20century%2C%20global%20powers%20have%20often%20used%20tariffs%20--%20as%20an%20economic%20weapon%20and%20a%20bargaining%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20brief%20history%20of%20tariff%20wars%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Corn%20Laws%20(1815-1846)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20Napoleonic%20Wars%2C%20Britain%20enacted%20the%20Corn%20Laws%20in%201815%20to%20protect%20its%20domestic%20agriculture%20by%20imposing%20high%20tariffs%20on%20imported%20grain.%20Landowners%20benefited%20from%20the%20Corn%20Laws%2C%20but%20it%20caused%20widespread%20hardship%20among%20the%20working%20class.%20The%20Anti-Corn%20Law%20League%2C%20led%20by%20Richard%20Cobden%20and%20John%20Bright%2C%20successfully%20mobilised%20public%20opinion%20against%20the%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20M%C3%A9line%20Tariff%20(1892)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrench%20Prime%20Minister%20Jules%20M%C3%A9line%20introduced%20the%20M%C3%A9line%20Tariff%20in%201892%20to%20shield%20the%20country's%20agriculture%20and%20industry%20from%20foreign%20competition.%20The%20tariff%20increased%20levies%20on%20imported%20grain%2C%20resulting%20in%20higher%20prices%20for%20domestic%20farmers%20while%20making%20food%20more%20expensive%20for%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Smoot-Hawley%20Tariffs%20(1930)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20Great%20Depression%2C%20President%20Herbert%20Hoover%20signed%20the%20Smoot-Hawley%20Act%20in%20June%201930.%20The%20act%2C%20intended%20to%20help%20American%20farmers%2C%20increased%20duties%20on%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20goods.%20The%20move%20prompted%20retaliatory%20measures%20from%20countries%20such%20as%20Canada%2C%20France%2C%20and%20Spain%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20sharp%20decline%20in%20global%20trade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Anglo-Irish%20Trade%20War%20(1932-1938)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETensions%20between%20Britain%20and%20Ireland%20escalated%20in%201932%20over%20unpaid%20land%20annuities.%20Britain%20put%20high%20tariffs%20on%20Irish%20agricultural%20exports%2C%20especially%20cattle%2C%20causing%20a%20significant%20hit%20to%20Ireland's%20economy.%20Ireland%20retaliated%20with%20duties%20on%20British%20coal%20and%20goods.%20The%20six-year%20dispute%20strained%20trade%20and%20worsened%20economic%20hardships.%20Later%2C%20a%201938%20settlement%20restored%20trade%20relations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Chicken%20War%20(1960s)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmerican%20chicken%20production%20skyrocketed%20after%20World%20War%20II%20and%20flooded%20the%20European%20markets%20with%20cheap%20poultry.%20European%20farmers%2C%20struggling%20to%20compete%2C%20urged%20their%20governments%20for%20protection.%20In%20response%2C%20the%20European%20Economic%20Community%20(EEC)%20imposed%20tariffs%20on%20US%20poultry%20imports%20in%201962.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Lumber%20War%20with%20Canada%20(1982-Present)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US-Canada%20softwood%20lumber%20dispute%20has%20been%20on%20for%20over%20four%20decades.%20America%20claims%20that%20Canada's%20government-controlled%20pricing%20system%20was%20an%20unfair%20subsidy.%20This%20disagreement%20has%20led%20to%20numerous%20tariffs%20and%20retaliatory%20measures%2C%20affecting%20trade%20relations%20between%20the%20two%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20US-Japan%20Auto%20Tariffs%20(1987)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20Ronald%20Reagan%20imposed%20100%25%20tariffs%20in%201987%20on%20%24300%20million%20worth%20of%20Japanese%20goods%2C%20primarily%20targeting%20the%20automotive%20sector.%20This%20move%20aimed%20to%20penalise%20Japan%20for%20failing%20to%20comply%20with%20a%20semiconductor%20trade%20agreement%20designed%20to%20increase%20US%20companies'%20access%20to%20the%20Japanese%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Banana%20War%20(1993-2012)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201993%2C%20the%20European%20Union%20put%20tariffs%20on%20Latin%20American%20bananas%2C%20effectively%20favouring%20producers%20from%20its%20former%20colonies%20in%20the%20Caribbean%20and%20Africa.%20The%20US%20challenged%20the%20EU's%20actions%20at%20the%20World%20Trade%20Organization%20(WTO)%20multiple%20times%2C%20securing%20favourable%20rulings%20each%20time.%20When%20the%20EU%20refused%20to%20lift%20the%20restrictions%2C%20the%20US%20retaliated%20by%20imposing%20tariffs%20on%20European%20luxury%20goods%2C%20including%20Scottish%20cashmere%20and%20French%20cheese.%20This%20trade%20dispute%2C%20dubbed%20the%20%26quot%3BBanana%20War%2C%26quot%3B%20dragged%20on%20for%20nearly%20two%20decades%20and%20ended%20in%202012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Steel%20War%20with%20Europe%20(2002)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20George%20W.%20Bush%20imposed%20tariffs%20ranging%20from%208%25%20to%2030%25%20on%20imported%20steel%20in%202002%20to%20protect%20the%20struggling%20US%20steel%20industry.%20In%20response%2C%20the%20EU%20threatened%20tariffs%20on%20%242.2%20billion%20worth%20of%20American%20goods%2C%20prompting%20Bush%20to%20lift%20the%20tariffs%20in%202003.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump's%20Trade%20War%20(2018)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20first%20term%2C%20Donald%20Trump%20imposed%20broad%20tariffs%20on%20solar%20panels%20and%20washing%20machines%2C%20followed%20by%20targeted%20tariffs%20on%20Chinese%20imports.%20In%20retaliation%2C%20China%20imposed%20tariffs%20on%20American%20agricultural%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743748620000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2F0seh0gro_donald-trump-announces-tariffs_625x300_03_April_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fbanana-war-to-trump-tariffs-a-brief-history-of-trade-wars-8083948%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Roughly%2019%20minutes%20into%20his%20speech%2C%20Trump%20was%20handed%20a%20rectangular%20board%20with%20a%20list%20of%20countries%20and%20regions%20and%20the%20tariffs%20they%20charged%20on%20America.%20The%20reciprocal%20tariffs%20US%20would%20charge%20henceforth.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fbanana-war-to-trump-tariffs-a-brief-history-of-trade-wars-8083948%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20led%20the%20removal%20of%20impeached%20South%20Korean%20President%20Yoon%20Suk%20Yeol%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743748332000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-119973335%2Cimgsize-94492.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fwhat-led-the-removal-of-impeached-south-korean-president-yoon-suk-yeol%2Farticleshow%2F119969589.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F119969589.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiat